Class Instances

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class Instances
extends weka.core.Instances

Instances class for parsing ARFF-encoded Web log files. This class overwrites Instances.initTokenizer(java.io.StreamTokenizer). In WEKA's implementation, '%' is interpreted as a comment character, while this is a valid character in URIs and thus in HTTP logs. If we wouldn't override the default Instances' behaviour, the ARFF data lines containing '%' as part of an URI would cause parsing errors.
